wikipedia_page.main: Joseph Thomas Marsden (11 October 1868 – 17 January 1887) was an English footballer who played for Darwen and Everton. He also earned one cap for the English national side in 1891.

response: For the Irish match, for which England selected a predominantly Midlands based team, another five players made their debut, of which Joseph Marsden of Darwen and Jem Bayliss of West Bromwich Albion (both defenders) were not selected again. The other débutantes were Alf Underwood of Stoke at left-back, George Cotterill of Cambridge University, who made the first of 4 appearances at centre-forward (scoring on his debut) and fellow forward Arthur Henfrey (Corinthian) (who also scored on his debut).  This was also Tinsley Lindley's final England appearance, which he marked by scoring 2 goals, as England were comfortable  6–1 victors.
